synoptic.model
Class PartitionGraph

java.lang.Object
  synoptic.model.PartitionGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
IGraph<Partition>
public class PartitionGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements IGraph<Partition>

This class implements a partition graph. Nodes are Partition instances, which are sets of messages -- ( LogEvent) -- and edges are not maintained explicitly, but generated on-the-fly by class Partition. PartitionGraphs can only be modified via the method apply which takes a object implementing IOperation. Operations must perform changes on both representations.

Author:
sigurd

initialEvents

private final java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.Set<LogEvent>> initialEvents
Holds the initial messages in this graph, grouped by the relation w.r.t. which they are initial. We keep track of initial partitions by keeping track of the initial messages but we need to do this for every relation, which is specified by the first argument to the hash-map.

terminalEvents

private final java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.Set<LogEvent>> terminalEvents
Holds the terminal messages in this graph. Like the initialMessages above, this hash-map maintains them w.r.t the relations.

Constructor Detail

PartitionGraph

public PartitionGraph(IGraph<LogEvent> g,
                      boolean partitionByLabel,
                      TemporalInvariantSet invariants)
Construct a PartitionGraph. Invariants from g will be extracted and stored. If partitionByLabel is true, all messages with identical labels in g will become one partition. Otherwise, every message gets its own partition (useful if only coarsening is to be performed).

Parameters:
g - The initial graph
partitionByLabel - Whether initial partitioning by label should be done
